All MAME ROMS as of MAME version 0.37 beta 5
--------------------------------------------
By Gordon Jefferyes
gjeffery@dircon.co.uk
29/07/2000 

For ZIP files fully merged just use the information as shown below.

For ZIP files split into individual games create the master ZIP file
with all the roms used by the master game.
Then create a separate ZIP for each clone game containing just
the roms used by the clone that do not appear in the master game.
This method may repeat some clone game roms.

For ZIP files split into individual games with no repeated roms
create the master ZIP file with all the roms used by the master game
and any roms used by more that one of the clones.
Then create a separate ZIP for each clone game containing just
the roms used by that clone.
This is a bit messy as the master game will not be a pure master set.

Some clone games use ROMs that are in the master game, but they use a
different name than that used by the master game. In this situation it is
not necessary to have two copies of the roms with different names.
Where this happens the extra clone roms are listed separately at the
bottom of each list for completeness, but are not required to be in
the ZIP files.
